title: Tropical storm watch discontinued for Hawaii and Maui Counties
text:
Tropical storm watch discontinued for Hawaii and Maui Counties Adv: 
Aug 06, 2015 Adv: 
Hawaii and Maui Counties are no longer under a tropical storm watch. The statewide flash flood watch has also been discontinued as Tropical Storm Guillermo continues to move north-west of the Hawaiian Islands. 
Due to potential moderate rainfall and high surf, some parks will be temporarily closed. 
This will be the final update from the HTA regarding the Tropical Storm Guillermo.
